<section id="gtkdialog"><title>GTKDialog</title>
<para>The GTKDialog class is a subclass of the
GTLWindow class (<xref linkend="gtkwindow" />).</para>

<para>It creates popup windows. These windows can be either modal or nonmodal.</para>

<section id="gtkdialoginit">
<title>Method: init</title>
<indexterm><primary>init</primary></indexterm>
<indexterm><primary>GTKDialog</primary>
<secondary>init</secondary></indexterm>
<para>Create a dialog with buttons.</para>
<para><emphasis role="bold">Syntax:</emphasis></para>
<programlisting>
<![CDATA[
>>--.GTKDialog~new(title, parent, flags--+--------------------+--)-------><
                                         | +---------------+  |
                                         | V               |  |
                                         +---, btext, bid--+--+
]]>
</programlisting>
<para><emphasis role="bold">Arguments:</emphasis></para>
<variablelist>
   <varlistentry>
      <term>title</term>
      <listitem><para>The dialog title.</para></listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
      <term>rxparent</term>
      <listitem><para>The parent window.</para></listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
      <term>flags</term>
      <listitem><para>The flags.</para></listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
      <term>btext</term>
      <listitem><para>The id or text (repeating).</para></listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
      <term>bid</term>
      <listitem><para>The response id (repeating).</para></listitem>
   </varlistentry>
</variablelist>
<para><emphasis role="bold">Returns:</emphasis></para>
<para>Zero.</para>
</section>

